10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Blue Prism is best suited for regulated industries, banking, government, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Levity, meanwhile, shines for document processing, email classification, content moderation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2001, Blue Prism describes itself as \"Enterprise-grade intelligent automation with digital workforce management.\" Levity, established in 2019, positions itself as \"No-code AI workflow automation for classifying text, images, and documents.\" With 18 years between them, Blue Prism brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Levity offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Blue Prism** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 8). However, this does not mean Levity is a poor choice — far from it. Levity excels in its own right, particularly for document processing and email classification.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value strong security and compliance focus, go with Blue Prism. If train custom ai classifiers without code matters more to you, Levity is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
